APIs is defined as application program interface, which can be a protocol, routine or any framework in a broader sense. 
In general, the API specifies how program contents should interact to each other, 
and therby aim to enrich the customer experience by enhancing the site functionality.
APIs can be quite diverse and unique depending on the business model or website goal at large.   
You can see multiple APIs illustrated on the Amazon interface: [I'm an inline-style link](https://www.amazon.com)
